The Mulliez family, which owns
Auchan supermarkets and other retail chains, is considering
bidding for the 34 French electronics stores being sold by  Metro
AG ,  Le Figaro  said, citing an executive working for the family.  An acquisition proposal will be presented to the executive
committee of HTM Group, a  Mulliez  company, on Nov. 5, said
Francis Cordelette, managing director of HTM, according to the
newspaper. HTM owns Boulanger and Electro Depot stores.  Dusseldorf, Germany-based Metro said yesterday that itâ€™s
